---
title: "_getAssetPrice - Price Resolution (Payment Abstraction V2)"
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB
    [*] --> q_check_streams: _getAssetPrice(asset) called
    q_check_streams --> q_check_fresh: dataStreamsFeedId configured for asset
    q_check_streams --> q_fallback_feed: no Streams feed configured
    q_check_fresh --> q_return_streams: streamsPrice.timestamp within stalenessThreshold
    q_check_fresh --> q_fallback_feed: streams price stale or missing
    q_return_streams --> [*]: return streamsPrice (normalized to feed decimals)
    q_fallback_feed --> q_query_feed: query usdDataFeed (Chainlink Data Feed)
    q_query_feed --> q_check_feed_stale: get latestRoundData from feed
    q_check_feed_stale --> q_check_feed_price: updatedAt within stalenessThreshold
    q_check_feed_stale --> q_revert_stale: feed data stale
    q_revert_stale --> [*]: revert StalePrice
    q_check_feed_price --> q_return_feed: price > 0
    q_check_feed_price --> q_revert_zero: price == 0
    q_revert_zero --> [*]: revert ZeroPrice
    q_return_feed --> [*]: return feedPrice

    note right of q_check_fresh
        INV-001: Streams prices take priority over Data Feeds when fresh
        INV-002: Staleness threshold is configurable per asset via FeedInfo
        INV-003: Price must be non-zero to be valid
        INV-004: dataStreamsFeedDecimals used to normalize Streams price to feed precision
    end note
